      "content": "The mechanisms for epigenetic changes are very real, and they show that environment can influence gene expression. However, translating a rare exposure into a predictable, functional \"upgrade\" in complex neural architecture overnight is a massive leap in biological probability. Most known functional neural changes, even those influenced by environment, happen gradually through learning and plasticity, not via instantaneous rewriting.",
